Persistant volumes (PV) and Persistent volume claims (PVC) manage data storage for pods 

Config Maps manage configuration settings for pods like environment (env )variables , URL’s and paths - basically all things not secrets 
- Instead of HARDCODING configurations because they change based off env , you store them in Config Maps keeping the app flexible 

 PV’s - data storage  Config Maps - configuration settings   
= make deployment of pods dynamic and flexible 


When using configs u can either pass them as env’s or you can mount them as volumes that point to the whole configMap 

